'''HomeBox ［ Box ］''' is a cross-platform "Box" [[Special:MyLanguage/Worlds|world]] created by Maebbie. The world is a large, curved glass box that reflects the skybox, creating an interesting and visually appealing environment.

[[File:HomeBox Spawn.jpg|thumb|The HomeBox Spawn ]]

==Design==

The HomeBox world is designed to be a simple yet optimized social space where users can hang out with friends in a lag-free environment. The curved glass box provides a unique and interesting backdrop for interactions.

===Features===

* Automatic mirror activation, seamlessly turning on when approached
* Swap between Light/Dark ambiance
* Toggle the "grid" mode (the legacy "old-style" of VRChat "Box" worlds)
* A shortcut to go to the mirror area
* Avatar toggle section available at the right side of the spawn area

==Popularity of "Box" worlds==

The HomeBox world is part of a larger trend in VRChat known as the "Box" worlds. These worlds are characterized by their simplicity, optimization, and focus on social interaction. Many users prefer simple designs that allow for easy navigation and lag-free experiences.

Box worlds are optimized for performance, ensuring a smooth experience for all users, especially those you have low-end equipment, and also prioritize social interaction instead of world interactions.

The "Box" world trend has become a part of VRChat culture, with many users creating their own Box worlds and participating in the community.